<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// encountered during extraction. It enables one to extract a sequence of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// values without error-checking and then checking for errors in bulk at the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// end. The class holds an Error object, so failing to check the result of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the parse will result in a runtime error. The error flag is sticky and</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// attempting to parse and without updating the Cursor offset. After clearing</Highlight></CodeLine>
